[code]    public static boolean Cmd(String str, String plr, int realID){
        int plrID = PlayerHandler.getPlayerID(plr);
        if(plrID != realID){return false;}//IMPOSSIBLE??? lolz .... sick joke? or is it? ~ sonis
        client pcis = (client) PlayerHandler.players[plrID];
        int totalLength = CommandsOrganizer.length;
        for(int i=0; i<=totalLength; i++){
            if(str.startsWith(CommandsOrganizer[i][0]) &&
                    pcis.playerRights == Integer.parseInt(CommandsOrganizer[i][1])){
                Events(str, plrID, Integer.parseInt(CommandsOrganizer[i][2]));
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }[/code]
Now if you were to compile, You'd get majority of only 2 errors. We need to add a method and an array.
Lets add the Array first. Its name will be mmm CommandsOrganizer and will be a double array.
